what: Run DESeq2 for multiple differential gene comparison.
title: Utility Functions To Deal Day To Day Bioinformatics Tasks.
code: res <- parcutils::run_deseq_analysis(counts = count_data ,                          sample_info = sample_info,                          column_geneid = "gene_id" ,                          log2fc_cutoff = 0.6,                          cutoff_pval = 0.05,                          group_numerator = c("treatment1", "treatment2") ,                          group_denominator = c("control"),                          column_samples = c("control_rep1", "treat1_rep1", "treat2_rep1", "control_rep2", "treat1_rep2", "treat2_rep2", "control_rep3", "treat1_rep3", "treat2_rep3"))

title: Categorize diff genes in to up and down based on log2FC, p-value and p-adj values. — categorize_diff_genes
text: Usually fold change 1.5 (log2FC ~0.6) statistical significance defined p /p.adj values considered mark gene differential expressed. However, cutoffs change based data quality. function allows changing cutoffs mark genes differently expressed. using package, time user need call function explicitly internally called run_deseq_analysis().

title: Generate a heatmap of normalised gene expression values, z-score or log2Fold-change values. — get_gene_expression_heatmap
text: Heatmap common tool show gene expression pattern across samples RNA-seq experiment. data exploration, common practice generate several heatmaps identify interesting patterns gene expression across sample. heatmap generating tools require data tabular form. However, prepare tabular form requires significant data wrangling sub-setting genes (rows) samples (columns) specifically RNA-seq studies studies consisting several samples replicates. function cut downs several steps data wrangling create heatmap gene expression, z-score log2 fold-change . Given object 'parcutils', names samples sample comprisons, genes show heatmap several arguments creates heatmap.output function output function ComplexHeatmap::Heatmap() can used functions ComplexHeatmap package.

title: Generate a heatmap of normalised gene expression values, z-score or log2Fold-change values. — get_gene_expression_heatmap
code: count_file <- system.file("extdata","toy_counts.txt" , package = "parcutils") count_data <- readr::read_delim(count_file, delim = "\t") #> Rows: 5000 Columns: 10 #> ── Column specification ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> Delimiter: "\t" #> chr (1): gene_id #> dbl (9): control_rep1, control_rep2, control_rep3, treat1_rep1, treat1_rep2,... #>  #> ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data. #> ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.  sample_info <- count_data %>% colnames() %>% .[-1]  %>%  tibble::tibble(samples = . , groups = rep(c("control" ,"treatment1" , "treatment2"), each = 3) )   res <- run_deseq_analysis(counts = count_data ,                          sample_info = sample_info,                          column_geneid = "gene_id" ,                          group_numerator = c("treatment1", "treatment2") ,                          group_denominator = c("control"),                          column_samples = c("control_rep1", "treat1_rep1", "treat2_rep1", "control_rep2", "treat1_rep2", "treat2_rep2", "control_rep3", "treat1_rep3", "treat2_rep3")) #> ℹ Running DESeq2 ... #> converting counts to integer mode #> Warning: some variables in design formula are characters, converting to factors #> estimating size factors #> estimating dispersions #> gene-wise dispersion estimates #> mean-dispersion relationship #> final dispersion estimates #> fitting model and testing #> ✔ Done. #> ℹ Summarizing DEG ... #> ℹ Done.  genes = parcutils::get_genes_by_regulation(x = res, sample_comparison = "treatment2_VS_control" , "both") get_gene_expression_heatmap(x = res, samples = c("control" ,"treatment1" , "treatment2"), genes = genes)   # plot raw expression values  get_gene_expression_heatmap(x = res, samples = c("control" ,"treatment1" , "treatment2"), genes = genes, convert_zscore = FALSE)   # plot log2 expression values  get_gene_expression_heatmap(x = res, samples = c("control" ,"treatment1" , "treatment2"), genes = genes, convert_zscore = FALSE,convert_log2 = TRUE)   # plot all replicates  get_gene_expression_heatmap(x = res, samples = c("control" ,"treatment1" , "treatment2"), genes = genes, convert_zscore = TRUE, summarise_replicates = FALSE)   # show gene names  get_gene_expression_heatmap(x = res, samples = c("control" ,"treatment1" , "treatment2"), genes = genes[1:10], convert_zscore = TRUE, summarise_replicates = FALSE , show_row_names = T)   # repair gene names  get_gene_expression_heatmap(x = res, samples = c("control" ,"treatment1" , "treatment2"), genes = genes[1:10], convert_zscore = TRUE, summarise_replicates = FALSE, show_row_names = T, repair_genes = T)   # fold change heatmap  get_fold_change_heatmap(x = res , sample_comparisons = c("treatment2_VS_control" ,"treatment1_VS_control") , genes = genes , cluster_columns = F , name = "Log2FC")

code: if (FALSE) { ref_file <- system.file("extdata", "Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.101.gtf.gz" ,package = "parcutils") ref_data <- rtracklayer::import(ref_file)  %>%  tibble::as_tibble() %>%  dplyr::mutate(seqnames = stringr::str_c("chr",seqnames ,sep = "")) %>% plyranges::as_granges()  ref_data_gr <-  ref_data %>% dplyr::filter(type == "gene" & gene_biotype == "protein_coding") query_regions_gr <- ref_data %>% dplyr::filter(type == "Selenocysteine")  %>% sample(5000)  oo <- plot_regions_relative_to_reference(query = query_regions_gr, reference  =  ref_data_gr)  oo$plot oo$data %>% ggplot2::ggplot(aes(x = q_relt_start)) + geom_density() }

DESeq2::DESeq() to perform DE analysis. — run_deseq_analysis
title:
Run differential expression (DE) analysis for several comparisosns at a time. Internally it uses
DESeq2::DESeq() to perform DE analysis. — run_deseq_analysis
text: DESeq2 popular method perform DE analysis RNA-seq data. Pre post DESeq run, however, involves several data wrangling steps. example, prior run DESeq genes may need filtered based number reads mapped genes across replicates. Similarly,  post DESeq run user needs set cutoffs (log2fc, pvalue padj) define regulated genes. large RNA-seq experiments involving several DE comparison sub-setting different cutoffs creates messy less readable code. function helps make things bit tidy increase code readability. Besides ,  output function can subsequently used several functions package.

title:
Run differential expression (DE) analysis for several comparisosns at a time. Internally it uses
DESeq2::DESeq() to perform DE analysis. — run_deseq_analysis
code: run_deseq_analysis(   counts,   column_geneid,   column_samples,   sample_info,   group_numerator,   group_denominator,   delim = "\t",   comment_char = "#",   min_counts = 10,   min_replicates = 1,   cutoff_lfc = 1,   cutoff_pval = 0.05,   cutoff_padj = 0.01,   regul_based_upon = 1,   ... )

title:
Run differential expression (DE) analysis for several comparisosns at a time. Internally it uses
DESeq2::DESeq() to perform DE analysis. — run_deseq_analysis
text: counts character string path count file object dataframe raw counts gene. See details know format count file count dataframe. column_geneid character string denoting column geneid counts column_samples character vector denoting names sample columns counts sample_info character string denoting name sample information file dataframe. file dataframe must least two columns without column names. First column denotes samples names second column denotes group name sample first column. e.g. group_numerator character vector denoting sample groups use numerator calculate fold change. group_denominator character vector denoting sample groups use denominator calculate fold change. delim character denoting deliminator count file. valid count file path. comment_char character denoting comments line count file. valid count file path. min_counts numeric value, default 10,  denoting minimum counts gene used o consider gene differential expression analysis. min_replicates numeric value, default 1, denoting minimum samples within group must minimum_counts. Value provided must higher number replicates group. example given values min_replicates = 2  minimum_counts = 10 genes minimum counts 10 least 2 sample groups used DEG. cutoff_lfc numeric value internally passed categorize_diff_genes cutoff_pval numeric value internally passed categorize_diff_genes cutoff_padj numeric value internally passed categorize_diff_genes regul_based_upon either 1, 2 3 internally passed categorize_diff_genes ... future use

title:
Run differential expression (DE) analysis for several comparisosns at a time. Internally it uses
DESeq2::DESeq() to perform DE analysis. — run_deseq_analysis
text: dataframe row differential comparison. total 8 columns explained . Column comp : stores name differential comparison row. Column numerator : stores name samples used numerator differential comparison row. Column denominator : stores name samples used denominator differential comparison row. Column norm_counts : named-list column. row column list two containing normalised genes expression values dataframe samples - numerator denominator. first column dataframe gene_id subsequent columns gene expression values replicates corresponding samples. normalised gene expression values obtained using  counts slot DESeqDataSet object. e.g.: counts(dds,normalized=TRUE) Column dsr : named-list column stores object class DESeq2::DESeqResults() differential comparison row. Column dsr_tibble:  named-listcolumn stores output DESeq2::DESeqResults() dataframe format differential comparison row. Column dsr_tibble_deg: data column column dsr_tibble except contains two extra columns signif regul. Values signif specifies statistical fold change significance gene values regul denotes whether gene regulated . Column deg_summmary : named-list column. element list dataframe summarizing number differential expressed gene differential comparison row.
